modules.description: Provides stack manipulation, arithmetic operations, and system command execution using a postfix notation. Works with integers, strings, and a stack-based data structure. Executes shell commands, performs calculations, and manages data flow in a linear, interactive environment.

The module provides operations for parsing and interpreting word lists, including handling loops, processing individual words, and managing stateful execution with error recovery. It works with custom types like `parser`, `interpreter`, `word`, and `value`, alongside arrays and strings, enabling tasks such as value conversion, comparison, and stack manipulation. Use cases include dynamic language interpretation, structured data parsing, and controlled execution of procedural commands.
